      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for the paper **\"The Internal State of an LLM Knows When It's Lying\"** by Amos Azaria and Tom Mitchell:\n\n## Paper Details\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper is authored by **Amos Azaria** and **Tom M. Mitchell**, and was published in **EMNLP (Findings) 2023, pages 967–976**."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The DOI is **10.18653/v1/2023.findings-emnlp.68**."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\nThe paper is available on:\n- **arXiv**: [arxiv.org/abs/2304.13734](https://arxiv.org/abs/2304.13734)\n- **ACL Anthology**: [aclanthology.org/2023.findings-emnlp.68](https://aclanthology.org/2023.findings-emnlp.68.pdf)\n- **OpenReview**: [openreview.net/forum?id=y2V6YgLaW7](https://openreview.net/forum?id=y2V6YgLaW7)\n\n## Summary\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "While LLMs have shown exceptional performance in various tasks, one of their most prominent drawbacks is generating inaccurate or false information with a confident tone. The authors provide evidence that the LLM's internal state can be used to reveal the truthfulness of statements, including both statements provided to the LLM and statements the LLM itself generates."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Their approach is to train a classifier that outputs the probability that a statement is truthful, based on the hidden layer activations of the LLM as it reads or generates the statement."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Experiments demonstrate that their trained classifier achieves an average of 71% to 83% accuracy labeling which sentences are true versus false, depending on the LLM base model."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "They also show that while LLM-assigned sentence probability is related to sentence truthfulness, this probability is also dependent on sentence length and word frequencies, resulting in their trained classifier providing a more reliable approach to detecting truthfulness."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The conference took place December 6–10, 2023."
      }
